WSJ Market Update Email

This script tries to recreate the visualization of index performance for 2021 up to Q3, including:

  • S&P 500

  • Nasdaq Composite

  • Dow Jones Industrial Average

Get Index Performance from 2021-01-01 to 2021-09-30

# Obtain Stock Prices from Yahoo! Finance via tidyquant

sp500 <- tq_get("^GSPC", get = "stock.prices", from = "2021-01-01", to = "2021-09-30")

nasdaq <- tq_get("^IXIC", get = "stock.prices", from = "2021-01-01", to = "2021-09-30")

djia <- tq_get("^DJI", get = "stock.prices", from = "2021-01-01", to = "2021-09-30")

Combine Stock Closing Prices

df <- bind_rows(
  sp500,
  nasdaq,
  djia
)

Calculate Percent changes from January 1, 2021

df <- df %>% 
  mutate(
    co_labels = case_when(
      symbol == "^GSPC" ~ "S&P 500",
      symbol == "^IXIC" ~ "Nasdaq Composite",
      symbol == "^DJI" ~ "Dow Jones Industrial Average"
    )
  ) %>% 
  group_by(symbol) %>% 
  mutate(
    pct_change = (adjusted - adjusted[1]) / adjusted[1]
  ) %>% 
  ungroup()

# write_rds(

Create Viz Part 1: Index Performance YTD

ggplot(
  df, 
  aes(
    x = date, 
    y = pct_change
    )
  ) +
  geom_line(
    color = "#036084"
  ) +
  geom_point(
    data = df %>% 
      group_by(symbol) %>% 
      slice(n()),
    color = "#036084",
    size = 1,
    aes(
      x = date,
      y = pct_change 
    )
  ) +
  geom_area(
    fill = "#EBF5FE"
  ) +
  facet_wrap(~ fct_rev(co_labels)) +
  theme(
    strip.background = element_blank(),
    strip.text.x = element_blank(),
    strip.text = element_blank()
  ) +
  # scale_x_date(
  #   date_breaks = "1 month",
  #   labels = c("Jan.", rep("", 7), "Sept.")
  # )
   scale_x_continuous(
    breaks = seq(
      as.Date("2021-01-01"), as.Date("2021-09-01"), by = "1 month"
      ), 
    labels = c("Jan.", rep("", 7), "Sept.")
  ) +
  theme_tufte(
    base_family = "Mukta"
  ) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)
  ) +
  theme(
    axis.ticks.y = element_blank()
  )

Create Viz Part 2: Inflation Mentions

df_infl <- tibble(
  qrtr = seq(
    as.Date("2018-01-01"), as.Date("2021-06-01"), by = "3 months"
    ) %>% 
    as.character() %>% 
    as_factor(),
  inflation_mentions = c(
    160, 164, 160, 163, 
    130, 125, 127, 140, 
    65, 70, 115, 148, 
    195, 224
  ),
  fill = c(
    rep("#78BEED", 13),
    "#0278AF"
  )
)


ggplot(
  df_infl, 
  aes(
    x = qrtr,
    y = inflation_mentions
    )
  ) +
  geom_col(
    aes(
      fill = fill
      ),
    width = 1
  ) +
  scale_x_discrete(
    breaks = c("2018-01-01", "2019-01-01", 
               "2020-01-01", "2021-01-01"),
    labels = c("2018", "'19", "'20", "'21")
  ) +
  scale_fill_identity() +
  scale_y_continuous(position = "right") +
  theme_tufte(
    base_family = "Mukta"
  ) +
  geom_hline(
    data = tibble(
      y = seq(50, 200, 50)
    ),
    aes(
      yintercept = y
    ),
    color = "#ffffff"
  ) +
  theme(
    axis.ticks.y = element_blank()
  )
